&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;mt4&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cylus is a cybersecurity startup, led by world-class cyber experts. Our mission is to protect millions of people, worldwide, from cyber threats specific to modern trains, keeping them safe and on time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cylus, the global leader in rail cybersecurity, helps mainline and urban railway companies avoid security incidents and service disruptions caused by cyberattacks. With over $50M in funding by top VCs and strategic investors, global customers, and strong partnerships with the biggest railway integrators, and some of the largest railroads as customers,&amp;nbsp; we make a significant impact on the multi-hundred-billion-dollar global railway industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a versatile, hands-on &lt;strong&gt;Marketing Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead and execute our global marketing activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage the full marketing calendar across campaigns, events, and content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee our digital presence, including website, social media, email marketing, and online brand consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute industry events and conferences, coordinating logistics, booth presence, speaking opportunities, and post-event follow-ups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive brand awareness across multiple channels with high-impact, creative marketing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute global marketing campaigns that align with company goals and support revenue growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with internal teams (Sales, Product, Leadership) to ensure messaging alignment and campaign effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with external partners and agencies to deliver campaigns, manage assets, and enhance brand reach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure and analyze campaign performance, reporting key insights, and optimizing future activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–3 years of proven experience in end-to-end marketing management, ideally within a B2B Tech startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with marketing tech tools, including CRM and marketing automation platforms (e.g., HubSpot, Salesforce, email marketing tools). High technical aptitude and experience using AI tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative capabilities including copywriting, visual design, content packaging, and the ability to independently create impactful online campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills in English—written, verbal, and presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to deep-dive and quickly learn new domains, technologies, products, and solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management skills, with the ability to multitask and make effective decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and measurement skills for producing in-depth lead-generation reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Big Plus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience from a Cybersecurity company&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

